## 📜 Section 4: Smart Contract Analysis

### Strengths
- ✅ Proper use of `@noupgrade async constructor()`
- ✅ `Mapping::get_or_use` for the counter
- ✅ Owner assertion (`assert_eq(info.owner, self.caller)`) on `grant_access` and `revoke_access`
- ✅ `file_record` and `access_record` as private records

### Weaknesses

| Issue | Description | Severity |
|-------|-------------|----------|
| No `purchase_file` | No on-chain payment mechanism | 🔴 CRITICAL |
| No file deletion | Owner cannot remove a file from listings | ⚠️ MEDIUM |
| No file metadata on-chain | Name and description only in localStorage | ⚠️ MEDIUM |
| No access verification function | Can't check on-chain if a user has access | ⚠️ MEDIUM |
| `revoke_access` doesn't burn records | Access records still exist even after revocation | ⚠️ MEDIUM |
| No event emission | No way to track transaction history | ⚠️ LOW |
| Price is `u64` only | No support for different token types | ⚠️ LOW |

### Missing Smart Contract Functions (Referenced in [proejct.md](file:///c:/Users/BMSIT/ShadowVault/proejct.md) but not implemented)

1. **`purchase_file()`** — No trustless payment flow
2. **`verify_access()`** — No on-chain access verification
3. **`delete_file()`** — No way to de-list a file

